primary.context: Caller has never logged into the owner portal before and needs a registration link
primary.detail: The agent verified the caller and sent a Clubhouse registration link to the updated email address provided.

steps: Caller requested help logging into their account.
Agent performed account lookup via phone number and verified identity with name and state.
Agent identified that the caller needed a new registration link for the Clubhouse portal.
Agent confirmed contact details; caller corrected the email address and phone number.
Agent confirmed the updated details and sent the registration link.
Caller confirmed satisfaction and the call was closed.

clarifications.note: Agent confirms if registration link is needed

corrections.note: Caller corrected email and phone number digits

insights.summary: The caller wanted to set up their owner account for the first time. The agent successfully verified the caller, updated their contact information, and sent a Clubhouse registration link.
